This paper is about a framework for optimizing multiple targets in recommender systems using deep Bayesian modeling. The paper involves machine learning techniques and optimization algorithms, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with recommendation systems, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves probabilistic modeling, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.DS, in that order.
